WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:20.360
L.A. Detective by Philip Brown.

00:20.360 --> 00:23.200
My name is Lenny Samuel.

00:23.200 --> 00:25.640
My friends call me Len.

00:25.640 --> 00:27.480
I'm a detective.

00:27.480 --> 00:30.160
I work in Los Angeles.

00:30.160 --> 00:33.600
I'm an L.A. detective.

00:33.600 --> 00:38.000
Everybody in Los Angeles is busy.

00:38.000 --> 00:41.080
But Len isn't busy.

00:41.080 --> 00:43.760
He's sitting in his office.

00:43.760 --> 00:45.880
He's waiting.

00:45.880 --> 00:48.960
He has no work today.

00:48.960 --> 00:52.320
Nothing is happening.

00:52.320 --> 00:57.120
Then a man comes into the office.

00:57.120 --> 01:00.800
Len doesn't know him.

01:00.800 --> 01:05.280
The man is short and dark.

01:05.280 --> 01:08.840
He's about 40 years old.

01:08.840 --> 01:12.040
He's wearing a suit.

01:12.040 --> 01:15.600
The man is holding a gun.

01:15.600 --> 01:20.320
The gun is pointing at Len.

01:20.320 --> 01:22.120
I'm Frank.

01:22.120 --> 01:23.880
Come with me.

01:23.880 --> 01:27.920
Mr. Blane wants to speak to you.

01:27.920 --> 01:31.080
I won't go with you, Frank.

01:31.080 --> 01:34.080
I don't like Mr. Blane.

01:34.080 --> 01:38.200
I don't want to speak to him.

01:38.200 --> 01:41.480
Frank is a tough man.

01:41.480 --> 01:43.520
He laughs.

01:43.520 --> 01:46.160
He hits Len on the head.

01:46.160 --> 01:48.880
He hits Len hard.

01:48.880 --> 01:51.720
Len's eyes close.

01:51.720 --> 01:54.520
Len falls down.

01:54.520 --> 01:58.680
He falls onto the floor of the office.

01:58.680 --> 02:04.320
Heh heh heh.

02:04.320 --> 02:06.600
Len wakes up.

02:06.600 --> 02:09.800
He opens his eyes.

02:09.800 --> 02:13.360
He's sitting in a big chair.

02:13.360 --> 02:16.640
The room is very warm.

02:16.640 --> 02:19.040
There are lots of plants in the room.

02:21.880 --> 02:23.720
Where am I?

02:23.720 --> 02:25.920
Hello, Mr. Samuel.

02:25.920 --> 02:28.920
Welcome to my house.

02:28.920 --> 02:33.200
An old man is talking and smiling.

02:33.200 --> 02:35.760
He's Mr. Blane.

02:35.760 --> 02:39.080
He's a very rich man.

02:39.080 --> 02:44.640
He's also a very bad man.

02:44.640 --> 02:48.680
You're going to help me, Mr. Samuel.

02:48.760 --> 02:52.080
You're going to find my daughter.

02:52.080 --> 02:55.960
Read these letters.

02:55.960 --> 02:59.120
Carmen is our prisoner.

02:59.120 --> 03:02.880
We want $100,000.

03:02.880 --> 03:04.960
Give us the money.

03:04.960 --> 03:08.520
Then Carmen will come home.

03:08.520 --> 03:12.080
Meet us on Tuesday at 2 p.m.

03:12.080 --> 03:15.400
Meet us at the bus station.

03:15.480 --> 03:19.480
The Young Ones.

03:19.480 --> 03:22.200
Father, help.

03:22.200 --> 03:25.120
Please give them the money.

03:25.120 --> 03:25.960
Carmen.

03:29.440 --> 03:31.640
Carmen is 18.

03:31.640 --> 03:34.320
She has long, dark hair.

03:34.320 --> 03:36.760
Her eyes are blue.

03:36.760 --> 03:39.520
She's beautiful.

03:39.520 --> 03:43.160
Mr. Blane gives Len a photo.

03:43.160 --> 03:44.640
He says,

03:44.640 --> 03:47.600
I want Carmen back.

03:47.600 --> 03:52.680
Go to the bus station at 2 o'clock on Tuesday.

03:52.680 --> 03:56.600
Frank has the $100,000.

03:56.600 --> 03:59.200
He's going with you.

03:59.200 --> 04:02.560
Give the money to The Young Ones.

04:02.560 --> 04:05.440
Bring Carmen home.

04:05.440 --> 04:09.720
I'll pay you $1,000.

04:09.720 --> 04:14.520
Len says, I don't like you, Blane.

04:14.520 --> 04:16.920
I don't want your money.

04:16.920 --> 04:19.320
But Carmen is in trouble.

04:19.320 --> 04:21.800
She needs help.

04:21.800 --> 04:22.800
I'll help her.

04:25.800 --> 04:29.200
It's 2 p.m. on Tuesday.

04:29.200 --> 04:33.560
Frank and Len are at the bus station.

04:33.560 --> 04:39.680
Frank has $100,000 in a bag.

04:39.680 --> 04:45.800
Large buses are going in and out of the bus station.

04:45.800 --> 04:49.160
There are lots of people.

04:49.160 --> 04:54.160
But Len can't see Carmen.

04:54.160 --> 04:57.400
Frank and Len wait.

04:57.400 --> 05:00.760
Then they see Carmen.

05:00.760 --> 05:04.240
She's standing by a bus.

05:04.240 --> 05:07.200
A young man is with her.

05:07.200 --> 05:13.040
The young man is holding Carmen's arm.

05:13.040 --> 05:14.760
Hello.

05:14.760 --> 05:17.640
Are you Carmen Blane?

05:17.640 --> 05:20.640
I'm working for your father.

05:20.640 --> 05:23.120
Who are you?

05:23.120 --> 05:26.280
I'm from The Young Ones.

05:26.280 --> 05:28.880
Where's the money?

05:28.880 --> 05:29.560
Here it is.

05:32.600 --> 05:35.960
Frank opens the bag.

05:35.960 --> 05:39.640
The young man sees the money.

05:39.640 --> 05:44.800
The young man lets go of Carmen's arm.

05:44.800 --> 05:48.200
Len holds Carmen's arm.

05:48.200 --> 05:53.520
Frank gives the bag of money to the young man.

05:53.520 --> 05:58.040
Suddenly, Carmen bites Len's hand.

05:58.040 --> 06:01.200
Len lets go of Carmen's arm.

06:01.560 --> 06:04.560
Ah!

06:04.560 --> 06:07.760
The young man hits Frank.

06:07.760 --> 06:10.200
Frank falls down.

06:10.200 --> 06:13.680
Ugh! Ow!

06:13.680 --> 06:19.040
Carmen and the young man jump onto the bus.

06:19.040 --> 06:22.240
The door of the bus closes.

06:22.240 --> 06:25.320
The bus drives off.

06:25.320 --> 06:29.480
It's going to San Francisco.

06:30.120 --> 06:33.440
Len can't get on the bus.

06:33.440 --> 06:37.320
He decides to get his car.

06:37.320 --> 06:41.360
Len decides to drive to San Francisco.

06:46.880 --> 06:49.880
Len is in his car.

06:49.880 --> 06:53.600
He's driving to San Francisco.

06:53.600 --> 06:57.760
He's going to find Carmen.

06:57.760 --> 07:02.680
Why is Carmen going to San Francisco?

07:02.680 --> 07:04.640
Who is the young man?

07:13.000 --> 07:15.360
It's Thursday.

07:15.360 --> 07:19.840
Len is in San Francisco.

07:19.840 --> 07:24.600
San Francisco is a big city.

07:24.600 --> 07:28.680
Len can't find Carmen.

07:28.680 --> 07:33.960
Suddenly, Len sees a sign on a building.

07:33.960 --> 07:38.720
The sign says, The Young Ones.

07:38.720 --> 07:43.120
The building is a school for poor children.

07:43.120 --> 07:47.080
Carmen is playing with the children.

07:47.080 --> 07:50.080
Len stops his car.

07:50.080 --> 07:56.240
He goes to speak to Carmen.

07:56.240 --> 07:58.480
I don't want to go home.

07:58.480 --> 08:00.520
I'm happy here.

08:00.520 --> 08:04.400
I like working at this school.

08:04.400 --> 08:08.800
The $100,000 is for the school.

08:08.800 --> 08:11.960
My father is a bad man.

08:11.960 --> 08:15.520
These papers show he is a criminal.

08:15.520 --> 08:19.280
Take the papers to the police.

08:19.280 --> 08:21.440
You stay here.

08:21.440 --> 08:23.840
Nobody will find you.

08:23.840 --> 08:27.320
I'll take the papers to the police.

08:27.320 --> 08:27.920
Good luck.

08:35.120 --> 08:37.520
It's Friday.

08:37.520 --> 08:41.000
Len is in Los Angeles.

08:41.000 --> 08:43.720
He's at the police station.

08:43.720 --> 08:49.520
Frank and Blane are at the police station, too.

08:49.520 --> 08:52.560
These papers show that you're a criminal, Blane.

08:55.960 --> 08:57.560
I'm tired.

08:57.560 --> 08:59.680
I have no money.

08:59.680 --> 09:02.360
But I have an exciting job.

09:02.360 --> 09:04.840
And I like to help people.

09:04.840 --> 09:08.400
That's why I'm an L.A. detective.
